==English==
===Nominal phrase===
'''two-seam fastball''' (plural: two-seam fastballs)

#{{baseball}} A [[pitch]] thrown with a grip in the "horseshoe" orientation of the ball, with the rotation at a slight angle resulting in an angled and slower rotation as compared to a four-seam fastball with similar velocity yielding a degree of sink to the [[pitch]]
#: ''His '''two-seamer''' has a heavy sink and keeps his infielders busy.''

